  "prompt": "Would Fitbit charge 2 function in the artic circle at - 35 degree?",
  "response": "The Fitbit Charge 2 is designed to operate in a wide range of temperatures, typically between 14\u00b0F and 113\u00b0F (-10\u00b0C to 45\u00b0C). Operating the device outside this range can potentially affect its performance and battery life. At -35\u00b0C, which is well below the minimum operating temperature, it's likely that the Charge 2 would not function properly or at all.\n\nIn extreme cold, battery performance can degrade significantly, and the device may not register movements or track metrics accurately. Additionally, the materials and electronic components may not withstand such low temperatures over extended periods.\n\nIf you plan to use your Fitbit Charge 2 in extremely cold environments like the Arctic Circle, it's advisable to keep the device as warm as possible (for instance, wearing it under your clothing) and to be aware that its functionality may be limited.",
